cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.HC 

The paper involves computer vision algorithms for image descriptor recognition, which suggests that it falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The application of the method in victim identification in mass disasters suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of radiographs also suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of computer graphics and computer-aided design (cs.GR) or computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CR). Finally, the potential use of the method in healthcare and dentistry suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
